inputs: 1. plaintext, 2. key of shifts
output: ciphertext

get command line argument from user for key
check if it is a positive integer digit (go back to step 4 if not)
    output an error message if not valid
convert string to int

get plaintext from user as string
shift each character by key
wrap back around from z to a if crossing z
if neither uppercase nor lowercase keep character the same
run until the end of the string

note:
does not shift punctuations
caps rules stay the same (i.e lowercase letter stays lowercase and uppercase stays uppercase)